cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about the emergence of language through multi-agent communication. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of a general AI through learning to communicate. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses reinforcement learning and differentiable relaxation to develop the communication protocol. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses neural networks to model the agents and their communication. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the properties of the resulting protocol, which are characteristic of natural languages, including sound.
